ular tour of the historical imagination and its universal traits.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHistoriography. 0aHistoryxMethodology. 0aHistoryxPhilosophy. 0aLanguage and history. 0aLiterature and history. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aFieweger, Mary Ellen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311074529040uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/31926040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477319284423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477319284/original  a978-3-11-074529-0  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK